transcription.text:
Speaker 1: I'm trying to get my volume on here, I don't know why I can't hear you.

Speaker 2: Okay, can you hear me now?

Speaker 1: Yes, how can I help you?

Speaker 2: I've got an order that I placed.

Speaker 1: I'm trying to get to the right picture here.

Speaker 2: I've got an order ID number that I need to discuss with you first of all.

Speaker 1: Are you ready for the ID number?

Speaker 2: What's your name and birthday?

Speaker 1: Mark Harrison, 8-19-1959.

Speaker 2: Thank you.

Speaker 1: Okay, I have your account up.

Speaker 2: What were you trying to do?

Speaker 1: First of all, I placed an order for 20 of your pills.

Speaker 2: When I got ready to check out, a little thing popped up and said I could add 10 more pills for $29.40 or something like that.

Speaker 1: Which I checked the box and it got charged, both of those charges, $63.95 and $29.40 got charged to my American Express, or my Capital One card.

Speaker 2: Okay, so $63 plus the $29, uh-huh.

Speaker 1: Yeah, so the $63 was for 20 pills I think.

Speaker 2: No, 63 was for 10.

Speaker 1: $63 was for 10?

Speaker 2: Yes, sir.

Speaker 1: That's $6.39 for a pill.

Speaker 2: So it's $49 and then the pharmacy charges themselves, they charge $14.

Speaker 1: Okay, so for 20 pills I got charged $80.92.

Speaker 2: Is that what you're telling me?

Speaker 1: That's right.

Speaker 2: That seems pretty expensive.

Speaker 1: So I sent a thing back in, I wanted to cancel my subscription, I didn't know I was on a subscription until I started reading some reviews.

Speaker 2: And so I sent out a thing on email and requested to cancel my thing.

Speaker 1: They said to call this number and, you know, finish taking me off the list or whatever it is.

Speaker 2: I can't, I'm not buying.

Speaker 1: Sure, no problem. I went ahead and paused your account out so you won't get any monthly prescriptions.

Speaker 2: But if you decide to get this medication or any of the other medications, you can do so by calling in or placing an order online with the doctor.

Speaker 1: So you have effectively canceled my subscription more or less is what I want?

Speaker 2: Yeah, you won't get any subscription monthly.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Alrighty.

Speaker 1: Anything else I can assist you with?

Speaker 2: That's it for now.

Speaker 1: Alrighty. Have a wonderful day. Bye-bye.

Speaker 2: Thank you.
